               <msContents>
                  <msItem class="#liturgica" n="1" xml:id="MS_Selden_Supra_40-item1">
                     <title key="work_13658" type="desc">Ordinal, Use of York</title>
                     <note>Order for feasts and ferial days during the second half of the liturgical year (from Septuagesima or Easter), arranged as the Sarum pye but less detailed; a set of mainly general rubrics (fol. 125v). Marginal references to a Synodus eboracensis.</note>
                     <incipit>A primum . Festum Pasche vij° Kalendas Aprilis, littera dominicalis A. Feria ija, ... iija, ... iiija, Festa duplicia . Feria quinta ... sexta, Sabbato Quasi ix lectiones . Dominica in octavis Pasche . Feria ija de feria Responsorium locutus est &#x0026; cetera</incipit>
                     <note>At end (fol. 125) are some special rules, and 'Explicit Tabula &#x0026; cetera'.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                 
               </msContents>
